{"id":938737842,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"2Â months","timestamp":1682308064,"status":11,"status_display":"Wrong Answer","runtime":"N/A","url":"/submissions/detail/938737842/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Sliding Subarray Beauty","memory":"N/A","code":"class Solution {\n    public int[] getSubarrayBeauty(int[] nums, int k, int x) {\n        int[] freq= new int[101];\n        int[] ans= new int[nums.length-k+1];\n        int idx=1;\n        for(int i=0;i<k;i++){\n            freq[50+nums[i]]++;\n        }\n        ans[0]=elementcheck(freq,x);\n        freq[50+nums[0]]--;\n        if(k==nums.length-1){\n            return ans;\n        }\n        int start=1;\n        for(int i=k;i<nums.length;i++){\n            freq[50+nums[i]]++;\n            ans[idx]=elementcheck(freq,x);\n            idx++;\n            freq[50+nums[start]]--;\n            start++;\n        }\n        return ans;\n    }\n    public int elementcheck(int[] freq,int x){\n       int ans=0;\n       for(int i=0;i<101;i++){\n           if(freq[i]>0){\n               x-=freq[i];\n           }\n           if(x<=0){\n               ans=i-50;\n               break; \n           }\n       }\n       if(ans>=0){\n           return 0;\n       }\n       return ans;\n\n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"sliding-subarray-beauty","has_notes":false}
